\section{First-person pronoun (I, me)}

Noun root: {\dn asmad} = asmad.\\

In English, some first-person pronouns start with an ``m'' sound, like
``me,'' ``my,'' and ``mine.'' A similar situation exists in
Sanskrit. (And in other languages, like Spanish, French, and
Italian.)\\

